figgy.title: Hide Raster resources that are children of RasterSets in Figgy search results
Generating a PDF the first time locks up a Passenger thread, eventually freezing up a Figgy machine.

comments.body: This caused Figgy to crash for 20 minutes on 1/11/22

Thoughts from Slack:

1. PDF Background Job + Form where they fill in an email for a notification.
2. Focus a couple boxes specifically to downloads so that manifests don't die for everyone when this freezes things up.
3. Receive a UV alert when a download is ready (takes 20 minutes)
4. Pre-generate all PDFs (most of these won't ever get downloaded)
5. Generate in the background and provide a progress bar (see https://groups.google.com/g/samvera-tech/c/yThEBMzA4_o/m/QTZUz-JYCAAJ)

orangelight.title: The accordion toggles for the filters present their role as "link" instead of button, and do not specify their state.

comments.body:
from https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/Accessibility/ARIA/Roles/button_role
- [x] add role="button" (so that we dont need to change the facet to a `<button>` or `<input type="button">`)
- [x] make the element focusable
- [ ] define event handlers for click and keydown events. (This includes handling the Enter and Space keypresses in order to process all forms of user input. See [the official WAI-ARIA example code](https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-practices/examples/button/button.html).)

orangelight.title: Type ahead matching field type - screen readers only say "edit text" when tabbing into fields that have no associated label

comments.body: Following notes in https://github.com/pulibrary/orangelight/issues/2821#issuecomment-1009118329 and @itmaybejj recommendation from the  developer.mozilla page `Warning: Be careful when marking up links with the button role. Buttons are expected to be triggered using the Space or Enter key, while links are expected to be triggered using the Enter key. In other words, when links are used to behave like buttons, adding role="button" alone is not sufficient. It will also be necessary to add a key event handler that listens for the Space key in order to be consistent with native buttons.` need to complete the 3rd checkbox before merging.
